Validate Triangle

Write a program to check whether a triangle is valid or not, when the three angles of the triangle are the inputs. A triangle is valid if the sum of all the three angles is equal to 180 degress .

Input Format

The first line contains an integer T, total number of testcases.

Then follow T lines, each line contains three angles A, B and C of triangle space seperated values.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 1000

Output Format

Display 'Yes' or 'No' if the triangle is Valid or not respectively.

Sample Input 0

1
40 40 100
Sample Output 0

Yes
Explanation 0

The angles are 40,40,100 which sums 180. as it is valid angle for a trangle print Yes on as output.
Sample Input 1

3
180 0 0
0 180 0
0 0 180
Sample Output 1

No
No
No

Solution:

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <math.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int i,a,b,c;
          int n;
    scanf("%d",&n);

while(n!=0){
        scanf("%d%d%d",&a,&b,&c);
        if((a>0) && (b>0) && (c>0)  )
        {
            if((a+b+c)==180)
            {
                
            printf("Yes");
             printf("\n");
            }
        
        else
        {
             printf("No");
            printf("\n");
           
        }
        }
    else
        {
             printf("No");
            printf("\n");
           
        }
    n--;
    }
    return 0;
}

